article.headline: Cleveland St. 59, Marist 44
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- J'Nathan Bullock scored 19 points and grabbed 13 rebounds and Cleveland State ended the game on a 13-0 run to beat Marist 59-44 on Saturday night. Norris Cole and Cedric Jackson chipped in with 10 points apiece for the Vikings (19-11). No Marist player scored in double figures as the Red Foxes only hit 30 percent of their shots from the field. Ryan Stilphen had nine points and 10 rebounds. Down 26-22 at the half, the Red Foxes (15-13) fell behind by 11 points early in the second half but pulled to within 46-44 on two free throws by Dejuan Goodwin with 4:42 left. But Bullock answered with a three-point play and teammate Breyohn Watson followed with a 3-pointer and the Vikings controlled play the rest of the way. The Red Foxes missed their last eight shots from the field and had three turnovers over the final 4:42.
